# compare(_:)

**Instance Method**

Compares the receiver with the specified date interval.

## Declaration

```swift
func compare(_ dateInterval: DateInterval) -> ComparisonResult
```

## Parameters

- **dateInterval**: The date interval with which to compare the receiver.

## Return Value

Returns an [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ComparisonResult] value that indicates the temporal ordering of the receiver and a given date interval:

- [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ComparisonResult/orderedAscending] if the receiver’s [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/startDate] occurs earlier than that of `dateInterval`, or both [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/startDate] values are equal and the [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/duration] of the receiver is less than that of `dateInterval`.
- [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ComparisonResult/orderedDescending] if the receiver’s [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/startDate] occurs later than that of `dateInterval`, or both [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/startDate] values are equal and the [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/duration] of the receiver is greater than that of `dateInterval`.
- [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ComparisonResult/orderedSame] if the receiver’s [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/startDate] and [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/duration] values are equal to those of `dateInterval`.

## Discussion

The following figure illustrates four `NSDateInterval` objects plotted on an arbitrary time axis. Each date interval spans its [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/duration] from left to right, from its [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/startDate] to its [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/endDate].



The result of comparing the date interval labeled **A** with the date interval labeled **B** is [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ComparisonResult/orderedAscending], because **A** has a [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/startDate] that occurs earlier than that of **B**.

The result of comparing the date interval labeled **C** with the date interval labeled **D** is [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/ComparisonResult/orderedDescending], because because **C** and **D** have the same [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/startDate], and **C** has a [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSDateInterval/duration] greater than that of **D**.

## Comparing Date Intervals

- **isEqual(to:)**: Indicates whether the receiver is equal to the specified date interval.
